{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Mozilla Firefox","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Glossary/Mozilla_Firefox","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>Mozilla Firefox <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">ist ein kostenloser Open-Source-<a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/Browser\">browser</a>, dessen Entwicklung von der Mozilla Corporation überwacht wird. Firefox läuft unter Windows, OS X, Linux und Android.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Erstmals im November 2004 veröffentlicht, ist Firefox mit Themes, Plug-ins und <a href=\"/en-US/Add-ons\">add-ons </a>vollständig an Benutzerbedürfnisse anpassbar. Firefox nutzt <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Gecko\">Gecko <small>(en-US)</small></a> um Websiten zu rendern und implementiert sowohl aktuelle, als auch demnächst anzuwendende Webstandards.</span></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"erfahren_sie_mehr","title":"<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Erfahren Sie mehr</span>","isH3":false,"content":"","titleAsText":"Erfahren Sie mehr"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"grundlegendes_wissen","title":"Grundlegendes Wissen","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"https://www.firefox.com/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Offizielle Seite von Mozilla Firefox</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"technische_referenzen","title":"Technische Referenzen","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/Firefox\">Documentation/developer info on MDN</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Erfahren Sie mehr</span>","id":"erfahren_sie_mehr"}],"summary":"Mozilla Firefox ist ein kostenloser Open-Source-browser, dessen Entwicklung von der Mozilla Corporation überwacht wird. Firefox läuft unter Windows, OS X, Linux und Android.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Mozilla Firefox","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/glossary/mozilla_firefox","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/glossary/mozilla_firefox/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Glossary","title":"Glossar"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Glossary/Mozilla_Firefox","title":"Mozilla Firefox"}],"pageTitle":"Mozilla Firefox - Glossar | MDN","noIndexing":false}}